Sentencas: This research aims to develop a better carbon resistant anode compared to conventional Ni-BCZY anode for methane fueled protonic ceramic fuel cell (PCFC).
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: Solid-state reaction process is used to prepare alloy Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode in PCFC.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: Ni is doped with Cu for better carbon resistance.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: Results show that, Ni0.9Cu0.1-BCZY anode calcined at 800 degrees C for 0.5 h exhibit an electrical conductivity of 2054 S/cm at 600 degrees C, which is 8.4% less than traditional Ni-BCZY anode.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: XPS, and Raman data show that Ni0.9Cu0.1-BCZY anode exhibit resistance to carbon deposition compared to traditional anode.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: The best carbon deposition resistance is observed for the Ni0.7Cu0.3-BCZY sample.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: This work demonstrates the sup-pression of carbon deposition and inhibition of anode deformation in methane fueled PCFC with Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode.
Titulo: Carbon resistant Ni1-xCux-BCZY anode for methane-fed protonic ceramic fuel cell

Sentencas: This work is helpful for development of carbon-resistant ma-terials for energy generation with solid oxide fuel cells.(c) 2022 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
